                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.4112/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-19T16:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>227. My telegram number 226, June 19, noon. Cummins states he will leave tomorrow
                    evening for Laredo. Am signing today inventory of effects, oaths and receipt for
                    strong room containing unknown archives to which King, British consul general,
                    will have access. Clerical staff British Legation, consisting of two persons,
                    will remain here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
